<div id="page">
  <h1>SGPA to Percentage SPPU</h1>
  <div class="mt-8 text-center">
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 text-center">
      Easily convert your Savitribai Phule Pune University (SPPU) grades from
      SGPA to their equivalent percentage values. This tool will assist you in
      converting your SGPA to a percentage and guide you on how to convert any
      SGPA value to its equivalent percentage.
    </p>
  </div>
  <form class="bg-white shadow-lg rounded-lg p-6 w-full max-w-sm mt-8">
    <h2 class="text-center text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
      SGPA to Percentage Calculator
    </h2>
    <div class="form-control mb-4">
      <label class="label">
        <strong>Enter SGPA:</strong>
      </label>
      <input
        type="number"
        id="sgpa"
        class="input input-bordered w-full"
        placeholder="Enter SGPA"
        step="0.01"
        min="0"
        max="10"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="form-control">
      <button
        type="button"
        id="calculate"
        class="btn bg-[#48ffb2] text-[#2c2c2c] mb-2">Calculate</button
      >
      <button type="reset" id="reset" class="btn btn-neutral">Reset</button>
    </div>
    <div id="result" class="mt-4 text-center text-xl font-semibold"></div>
  </form>
  <div
    id="additional-content"
    class="bg-[#fff] text-[#2c2c2c] p-6 mt-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg"
  >
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
      What is a SGPA to Percentage Calculator?
    </h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-left leading-relaxed">
      SGPA which stands for Semester Grade Point Average is a very popular
      method to calculate the students grades. This grading system is widely
      used in many universities of the India.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-left leading-relaxed mt-4">
      SGPA is calculated based on the grades obtained in the individual subject
      and credit assigned to each subject.
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8">
      How to Convert SGPA to Percentage SPPU?
    </h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-left leading-relaxed">
      The formula used to convert SGPA to Percentage is <strong
        >Percentage = (SGPA x 10) - 7.5</strong
      >. Therefore, to convert SGPA to percentage, follow these steps:
    </p>
    <ol class="text-lg text-left leading-relaxed">
      <li class="p-2">
        <strong>Step 1: </strong>In the first step, multiply the SGPA value by 10.
      </li>
      <li class="p-2">
        <strong>Step 2: </strong>Then, subtract 7.5 from the result obtained
        from the first step.
      </li>
      <li class="p-2">
        <strong>Step 3: </strong>This will give you the equivalent score in
        percentages.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8">SGPA Grading Table</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="table table-zebra w-full border border-[#48ffb2]">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th
              class="bg-[#48ffb2] text-[#2c2c2c] border border-[#48ffb2] text-left"
              >Letter Grade</th
            >
            <th
              class="bg-[#48ffb2] text-[#2c2c2c] border border-[#48ffb2] text-left"
              >Percentage</th
            >
            <th
              class="bg-[#48ffb2] text-[#2c2c2c] border border-[#48ffb2] text-left"
              >Grade Point</th
            >
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">O</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">91-100%</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">10</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">A+</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">81-90%</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">9</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">A</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">71-80%</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">8</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">B+</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">61-70%</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">7</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">B</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">51-60%</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">6</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">C</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">41-50%</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">5</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">F</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">Below 40%</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">0</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">AB</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">Absent</td>
            <td class="border border-[#48ffb2]">0</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
  <style>
    body {
      text-align: center;
    }

    #page {
      padding: 2rem;
      width: 100%;
      min-height: 100vh;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      flex-direction: column;
      background: #f5fffa;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 4rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      font-weight: 900;
      text-align: center;
      color: #2e2b23;
    }

    /* Responsive */
    @media only screen and (max-width: 576px) {
      h1 {
        font-size: 40px;
        line-height: 50px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</div>
